data.value: About VibeBot This program convert stereo wave files to stereo mp3 files. Files are encoded with the samplerate of 44100 Hz (44.1kHz) The result are 320kBits/s high quality audio files. The convertetd files will be normalized at the given value, without any loss of data. After that, track artist and title is written into the metadata. This is called tagging. Tagging will only be succsessfully, if the filename is in the required synthax. For example: Dj Reverb - Hydra 'Dj Reverb' is the artist and 'Hydra' the title, the elements are seperated by a hyphen.
